Detailed Description

This struct defines the parameters for geomtery of the sinogram
Parameters:
frameStartTime frame start time yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss
scanStartTime yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss, time beginning of scan
duration duration of frame
isotope Radioisotope descripor, i.e. "F-18"
halflife Halflife of radioisotope in 1/sec
positronFraction fraction of positron emitted by the isotope
decayCorrectionTime yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss, time for start of decay correction
studyDirectory This is needed because the mu images are stored there
frameDirectory directory for output files
listmodeFilename full path, from study table
xmlFilename as defined, with full path
studyDescription as defined, from database
outputFileNameBase output file name base, without path or extensions
outputFileType Determines output file format
outputDataType Output Image Datatype like "int16", "int32", "float32", "float64"
frameNumber frameID in Frames table: 0,1,2,...
startingIteration Requested beginning iteration number; -1 is default
usePreviousResult If true, indicates that we should try to start from an earlier iterate (other than zero)
scaleStartingImage If true, indicates that we should scale the output image controls whether initializationlogic is applied, i.e., if scaleStartingImage is true, the input image will be scaled to be consistent with the data. If scaleStartingImage is false no image scaling will occur. If usePreviousResult is true, then scaleStartingImage should be set to false. default is true when usePreviousResult=false
useStartingImage - for backward compatibility
startingImage If exists, we read in this as a starting image.Note that this image extension should be consistent with the extensions structure
inputLLD Lower level discrimination from header file
lookForZero whether to look for zero time in the listmode file
enableBoundsCheck whether to perform a preliminary pass to set bounds of each line of response
verbosity Frame verbosity. Will be overriden by the individual parameter verbosity
scratchPath path of HRRT scratch space
processWholeFile determines whether the frame should process the whole file
